Financial Health Dashboard
Overview

The Financial Health Dashboard is an interactive Power BI project developed as part of my internship. The dashboard provides real-time insights into an organization's financial performance by analyzing income statements, balance sheets, cash flows, profitability trends, and financial forecasts. It is designed to help small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) make informed financial decisions through interactive visualizations.

Objective

The objective of this project is to analyze an organization's financial health by providing real-time insights into key financial metrics, profitability, and future financial planning using interactive Power BI dashboards.

Key Features

Income Statement Analysis
Monitor revenue, expenses, gross profit, and net profit.
Compare financial performance across different periods.
Track profit margins and business growth.

Balance Sheet Analysis
Analyze assets, liabilities, and equity.
Evaluate the company's financial position.
Monitor liquidity and financial stability.

Cash Flow Analysis
Visualize operating, investing, and financing cash flows.
Track cash inflows and outflows over time.
Assess cash availability for business operations.

Profitability Analysis
Analyze profit trends across multiple periods.
Compare revenue growth and expense patterns.
Evaluate key financial performance indicators (KPIs).

Financial Forecasting
Forecast future revenue and expenses.
Support budgeting and financial planning.
Enable proactive business decision-making using predictive analysis.

Dashboard Insights
Revenue and expense trends.
Gross profit and net profit analysis.
Cash flow performance.
Balance sheet overview.
Profitability trends over time.
Financial forecasting for budgeting and planning

